<DOC><DOCNO> AP890410-0241 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-10-89 1932EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-HenleyPurchase 1stLd-Writethru   04-10 0208</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Henley Purchase, 1st Ld-Writethru,0231</SECOND><HEAD>Henley Group Buys Defense Conglomerate</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: SUBS 5th graf to CORRECT that $100 million was total contribution.</HEAD><DATELINE>HAMPTON, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Henley Group Inc. said Monday it would buythe 50 percent stake in PA Holdings Inc. it does not already ownfor $165 million from Wasserstein, Perella andamp; Co., its partner inthe 1988 buyout of the aerospace and defense company.   A purchase agreement was completed during the weekend, Henleyspokesman Norman Ritter said Monday. The final sale would becompleted after the Henley board gives its approval, he said.   Henley has had operating responsibility for PA Holdings since itteamed with Wasserstein Perella, a New York investment firm, to buythe company from Whitman Corp. in a $1.2 billion leveraged buyoutlast August.   In a leveraged buyout, a company is bought with mostly borrowedfunds, which are then repaid from the firm's cash flow or the saleof its assets.   Henley and Wasserstein Perella contributed a total of $100million to the buyout.   PA Holdings designs and makes aircraft flight-control actuationsystems, hydrugh Cleveland Pneumatic Co., PA Holdings designs,develops, makes and overhauls landing gear for commercial andmilitary aircraft.   PA Holdings had approximately $1 billion in sales in 1988.</TEXT></DOC>